loud /laʊd/

(louder,loudest) 

1. ADJ If a noise is loud , the level of sound is very high and it can be easily heard. Someone or something that is loud produces a lot of noise. 大声的; 吵闹的 

例： Suddenly there was a loud bang. 突然砰地一声响。 

例： His voice became harsh and loud. 他的声音变得又尖又响。 

2. ADV Loud is also an adverb. 大声地; 吵闹地 [ADV after v] 

例： She wonders whether Paul's hearing is OK because he turns the television up very loud. 她怀疑保罗的听力有问题，因为他把电视机的音量调得很大。 

3. loudly ADV 大声地; 吵闹地 [ADV with v] 

例： His footsteps echoed loudly in the tiled hall. 他的脚步声响亮地回荡在铺着瓷砖的大厅里。 

4. ADJ If you describe something, especially a piece of clothing, as loud , you dislike it because it has very bright colours or very large, bold patterns which look unpleasant. (尤指衣服) 花哨的 [表不满] 

例： He liked to shock with his gold chains and loud clothes. 他喜欢戴金链子，穿花哨衣服，以此制造轰动。 

5. PHRASE If you say or read something out loud , you say it or read it so that it can be heard, rather than just thinking it. 出声地 

例： Even Ford, who seldom smiled, laughed out loud a few times. 即使是平时不苟言笑的福特也好几次笑出了声。

